  <action><if><agent-running name='&attributes:name;' />
	      <then><em>installed</em> <get name="content"/></then>
	  </if></action>
</define>

<hr />
<h3><a name='agents'>Standard Agents</a></h3>
<dl>
  <dt> <a name='Proxie'>Proxie agent</a>
       <installed name="Proxie"/></dt>
  <if><agent-running name='Proxie'/><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/load-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Load' />
       src: <input name='src' value='./Proxie/AGENT.xml' />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  <dt> <em>Proxie Sub-agents</em> </dt>
  <dd> <dl>
	 <dt> <a name='History'>History agent</a>
	      <installed name="History"/></dt>
	 <if><agent-running name='History' /><else>
	 <dd> <form action='/Admin/load-agent' method='POST'>
	      <input type='submit' value='Load' />
	      src: <input name='src' size="30"
	      	          value='./Proxie/History/AGENT.xml' />
	      </form></dd></else></if>
	 <dt> <a name='Toolbar'>Toolbar agent</a>
	      <installed name="Toolbar"/></dt>
	 <if><agent-running name='Toolbar' /><else>
	 <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/load-agent' method='POST'>
	      <input type='submit' value='Load' />
	      src: <input name='src' size="30" 
	      	          value='./Proxie/Toolbar/AGENT.xml' />
	      </form></dd></else></if>
	 <dt> <em>Toolbar sub-agents:</em></dt>
	 <dd> <dl>
		<dt> <a name='remoteTools'>remoteTools agent</a>
		     <installed name="remoteTools"/></dt>
		<if><agent-running name='remoteTools'/><else>
		<dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
		     <input type='submit' value='Load' />
		     src: <input name='src' size="30" 
	      	         	 value='./Proxie/remoteTools/AGENT.xml' />
		     </form></dd></else></if>
		<dt> <a name='fileTools'>fileTools agent</a>
		     <installed name="fileTools"/></dt>
		<if><agent-running name='fileTools'/><else>
		<dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
		     <input type='submit' value='Load' />
		     src: <input name='src' size="30" 
	      	         	 value='./Proxie/fileTools/AGENT.xml' />
		     </form></dd></else></if>
	      </dl></dd>
	 <dt> <a name='Cache'>Cache agent</a>
	      (keeps a copy of every external doc...)
	      <installed name="Cache"/>
	 <if><agent-running name='Cache'/><else>
	 <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
	      <input type='submit' value="Create" />
	      name:<input name='agent' value='Cache' />
	      path: <input name='path' value='Proxie' /><br />
	      (could add more options here, like update frequency: always, never,
	      once,...) 
	      </form> </dd></else></if>
       </dl>

  <dt> <a name='Demo'>Demo</a>
       (Active Document Demonstration and Test agent)
       <installed name="Demo"/></dt>
  <if><agent-running name='Demo' /><else>
  <dd> <FORM action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Load' />
       src: <input name='src' size="30" value='./Demo/AGENT.xml' />
       </FORM></dd></else></if>

  <dt> <a name='View'>View agent</a>
	      <installed name="View"/></dt>
  <if><agent-running name='View'/><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/load-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Load' />
       src: <input name='src' size="30" value='./View/AGENT.xml' />
       </form></dd></else></if>

  <dt> <a name='Swifty'>Swifty</a>
       (from tutorial: illustrates how to create an agent)
       <installed name="Swifty"/></dt>
  <if><agent-running name='Swifty' /><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value="Create" />
       name:<input name='agent' value='Swifty' /><br />
       </form> </dd></else></if>

</dl>

<hr />
<h3><a name='DOFS'>Document-Oriented File Systems</a></h3>

<p> DOFS agents provide basic file browsing capabilities; their function is to
    serve local files.  They are usually created, using the form below, rather
    than being loaded from XML files. 

<dl>
  <dt> <a name='dofs'>the DOFS agent</a></dt>
  <dd> <if><agent-running name='DOFS' />
       <then><em>is already running, as it should be.</em></then>
       <else> Really needs to be running, or lots of things won't work.
       <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Install NOW!' />
       name:<input name='agent' value='DOFS' />
       </form></else></if><p>

  <dt> <a name='My'>DOFS/My</a> is no longer needed:</dt>
  <dd> <a href='/~/'>/~/</a> (the <a href='/ROOT'>ROOT</a> agent's data
       directory) has replaced it.
       
  <dt> <a name='PIA'>DOFS/PIA</a> <installed name="PIA"/></dt>
  <if><agent-running name='PIA' /><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='PIA' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='&piaDIR;/Doc' />
       <input type='submit' value="Create" />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  <dt> <a name='PIA'>DOFS/Doc</a> <installed name="Doc"/></dt>
  <if><agent-running name='Doc' /><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='Doc' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='&piaDIR;/Doc' />
       <input type='submit' value="Create" />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  <dt> <a name='Home'>DOFS/Home</a> (possible security hole)
        <installed name="Home"/></dt>
  <if><agent-running name='Home'/><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='Home' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='~/' />
       <input type='submit' value="Create" />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  <dt> <a name='Root'>DOFS/Root</a> (probable security hole)
        <installed name="Root"/>
  <if><agent-running name='Root'/><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='Root' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='/' />
       <input type='submit' value="Create" />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  <dt> Generic DOFS form:  </dt>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='Name' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='/complete/path/' />
       <input type='submit' value="Create" />
       </form>
       </dd>
</dl>

<hr />
<h3><a name="load">Generic Form for loading an agent</a></h3>

<dl>
  <dt> This form ``loads'' an agent's data structure from an XML file. </dt>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/load-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value="Load" />
       <b>File:</b><input name="src" size="30" value="./.../AGENT.xml" />
       </form>

       Normally the file that defines an Agent has the name
       <code>AGENT.xml</code>.
       </dd>
</dl>

<hr />
<h3><a name="create">Generic Form for creating an agent</a></h3>

<dl>
  <dt> This form ``creates'' an agent data structure by directly specifying
       its attributes.  </dt>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/create-agent' method='POST'>
       <table>
         <tr><th><input type='submit' value="Create" /></th>
             <th>Name:</th><td><input name='agent' value='' /></td></tr>
         <tr><th>&nbsp;</th>
             <th>Type:</th><td><input name='type' value='' /></td></tr>
         <tr><th>&nbsp;</th>
             <th>Path:</th><td><input name='path' value='' /></td></tr>
         <tr><th>&nbsp;</th>
             <th>Home:</th><td><input name='home-dir' value='' /></td></tr>
         <tr><th>&nbsp;</th>
             <th>Data:</th><td><input name='data-dir' value='' /></td></tr>
       </table>
       </form>

       Everything but the Name is optional.  Home, User, and Data directories
       only need to be specified if they differ from the defaults, which are
       derived from the Agent's pathname (path/name).
       </dd>
</dl>

<hr />
<h3><a name="about">About agent installation</a></h3>
 
<p> An Agent is represented in the information Agency by a persistent software
    object.  In order for the Agency to know about an Agent and direct
    requests like <code> http://localhost:8888/Agent/home </code> to an
    <code>Agent</code>, the agent must be ``<em>installed,</em>'' which
    creates the corresponding software object.</p>

<p> There are actually two ways to install an Agent: one is to ``<a
    href="create-agent">create</a>'' it, given a few standardized
    attributes.  The other is to ``<a href="load-agent">load</a>'' its entire
    data structure from an XML description file.</p>

<p> When the Agency is started, it creates an <a href="/Admin">Admin</a>
    agent, which initializes itself by loading its <code>initialize.xh</code>
    file.  This, in turn, looks for a file called <code><a
    href="agent-files.xml">agent-files.xml</a></code>.  If it exists, it
    specifies a list of XML files to load. </p>

<p> If there is no <code>agent-files.xml</code> to load, the Admin agent looks
    in the Agency's <code><a href='START-UP.html'>START-UP.html</a></code> and
    submits any agent-creation forms found there. </p>

<p> Other agents can be installed using this form which contains ``canned''
    install forms for various agents.  You can paste sections out of this file
    into your own <code> START-UP.html </code> file.  When you design a new
    agent, you can add a default install form to this page.</p> 

